Preheat your oven to 200°C and bring a #saucepan{} of water with @salt{pinch} to
the boil. Peel the @potatoes{450}(peeled and chopped into 2cm chunks) and add to
the pan of boiling water. Cook until you can easily slip a knife through,
~{15-20%minutes}. Drain in a #sieve{} and return to the saucepan (off the heat).
Add a knob of @butter{knob} and a splash of @milk{splash}(if you have some) and
mash with a #potato masher{} until really smooth. Cover with a #lid{} and set
aside.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.
Season the @lamb rump{250} all over with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. When
hot, add the lamb (skin-side down) to the pan. Fry until golden all over,
turning occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a #baking tray{} (keep the
pan!). Roast for 2P/4P: ~{12-15%minutes}, 3P: ~{15-18%minutes} (for
medium-rare). Cook for ~{5-10%minutes} more for well done. When cooked, cover
loosely with #foil{}, set aside and allow to rest.

Halve, peel and finely chop the @eschalion shallot{1}(halved, peeled and finely
chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Pick the mint leaves from their stalks and finely chop the
@mint{1}(leaves picked and finely chopped) (discard the stalks). Finely chop
the @flat leaf parsley{1}(finely chopped with stalks) (stalks and all). Roughly
tear the @shitake mushrooms{50}(roughly torn). Return the now empty frying pan
to medium-high heat. Stir in the @red wine stock paste{14} and
@water{150%for the sauce}, boil then lower the heat and simmer until glossy,
~{4-5%minutes}.

While the sauce reduces, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in another large frying
pan on medium-high heat. When hot, add the shallot and shitakes and fry until
golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook, ~{1%minute}. Stir in the
@baby spinach{125} a handful at a time to wilt then remove the pan from the
heat.

Once the lamb has rested for a few minutes, gently reheat anything that needs it
over a low heat and get ready to serve! Stir half the herbs through the
mushrooms and spinach and the remainder through the sauce. Season everything to
taste with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

To serve, spread a small amount of potato purée on your plates. Carve the lamb
(stir any resting juices into the sauce) and sit it on top of the purée.
Arrange the mushrooms and spinach all around then drizzle over the red wine
sauce. Enjoy!